## Typography

### Font Families

**Primary Font: Inter** (or Geist Sans as fallback)
- Purpose: All UI text—headings, body, labels
- Weight range: 400 (regular) to 700 (bold)
- Fallback stack: `Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif`

**Monospace Font: Fira Code or IBM Plex Mono**
- Purpose: Code snippets, data values, amounts, technical information
- Usage: Display only, never use for body text
- Example: `$2,450.00` or `API_KEY_12345`

### Type Scale

All text must use one of these sizes. Do not create custom sizes.

```
12px (xs) - Small labels, captions, helper text
14px (sm) - Secondary text, small body text, metadata
15px (base) - Default body text, most content
16px (md) - Form labels, secondary headings
18px (lg) - Section headings, emphasis
20px (xl) - Page section headers
24px (2xl) - Page titles, major headings
28px (3xl) - Hero headings (rare)
32px (4xl) - Main page headings (rare)
```

### Font Weights

Use only these weights. Do not use intermediate weights.

- 400: Body text, regular content (most common)
- 500: Emphasized body text, slightly heavier labels
- 600: All headings, prominent labels, emphasis
- 700: Strong emphasis, hero text (use sparingly)

### Heading Hierarchy

**H1 (32px, 700 weight)**
- Purpose: Page title only. Maximum one per page.
- Example: "Dashboard" or "Manage Services"
- Spacing: 32px bottom margin

**H2 (24px, 600 weight)**
- Purpose: Section titles within a page
- Example: "Recent Jobs" or "Account Settings"
- Spacing: 24px bottom margin, 32px top margin

**H3 (18px, 600 weight)**
- Purpose: Subsection titles, card titles
- Example: Card headers, form section titles
- Spacing: 16px bottom margin

**H4 (16px, 600 weight)**
- Purpose: Form labels, small section headers
- Example: Input labels, list item headers
- Spacing: 12px bottom margin

**Body Text (15px, 400 weight)**
- Purpose: All readable content
- Line height: 1.6 (24px)
- Letter spacing: 0px (default)
- Spacing: 16px paragraph margin

**Small Text (12px, 400 weight)**
- Purpose: Helper text, captions, metadata
- Line height: 1.5 (18px)
- Example: "Last updated 2 hours ago"

### Typography Rules

**DO:**
- Use consistent font sizes from the scale
- Maintain clear hierarchy: headings darker than body, body darker than helpers
- Set line height to 1.6 for body text (improves readability)
- Use 600 weight for all headings and emphasis
- Add 16-24px bottom margin to headings

**DON'T:**
- Mix fonts within a section (stick to Inter for UI)
- Use font sizes not in the type scale
- Use weights other than 400, 500, 600, 700
- Create custom line heights (use system defaults)
- Use all caps for body text (use for labels only)
- Stack multiple headings without body text between them

