## Spacing & Layout

### Spacing Grid

All spacing must be a multiple of 8px. This is the fundamental unit.

```
4px   - Micro spacing (rare, only for fine adjustments)
8px   - Smallest standard unit (gaps, tight spacing)
16px  - Standard unit (default padding, margins)
24px  - Medium spacing (section separation, larger gaps)
32px  - Large spacing (major section breaks)
40px  - Extra large (rare)
48px  - Hero sections, major breaks
64px  - Page sections, very large gaps
80px  - Hero spacing (rare)
96px  - Extreme spacing (almost never used)
```

### Component Padding

**Buttons**
- Horizontal padding: 16px
- Vertical padding: 12px (40px total height)
- Border radius: 8px (not overly rounded)

**Input Fields**
- Horizontal padding: 12px
- Vertical padding: 10px
- Height: 40px
- Border radius: 8px

**Cards**
- Padding: 24px (all sides)
- Border radius: 12px
- Gap between items inside: 16px

**Form Fields**
- Label spacing: 8px above input
- Helper text spacing: 4px below input
- Gap between form fields: 16px

### Layout Constraints

**Max Content Width: 1440px**
- Use for dashboard content areas
- Content area should be centered with equal margins on sides
- Never exceed this width for readability

**Sidebar Width: 280px (expanded)**
- Sidebar width when expanded
- Collapsed width: 80px (icons only, no labels)
- Transition smoothly between states (0.3s)

**Column Grid**
- Desktop: 12-column grid (each column ~120px at max width)
- Tablet: 8-column grid
- Mobile: 4-column grid
- Gutter: 16px between columns

### Spacing Rules

**DO:**
- Always use multiples of 8px
- Maintain consistent spacing throughout
- Use 24px padding for cards
- Use 16px for standard gaps between elements
- Add generous whitespace around important content

**DON'T:**
- Use arbitrary spacing values (1px, 3px, 5px, 7px, etc.)
- Create padding that isn't a multiple of 8
- Cram too much content together (allow breathing room)
- Use inconsistent spacing for similar elements
- Forget to account for spacing when responsive design

