## Accessibility Requirements

### Color Contrast

All text must meet these standards:

- Normal text (14px+): 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum
- Large text (18px+, 600 weight+): 3:1 contrast ratio minimum
- Graphics and UI components: 3:1 contrast ratio
- Test with: WebAIM contrast checker or axe DevTools

### Touch Targets

All interactive elements must meet accessibility standards:

- Minimum size: 44x44px (mobile)
- Desktop buttons: 40x40px minimum
- Link text: Underlined or otherwise distinguished
- Spacing: At least 8px between touch targets

### Keyboard Navigation

All functionality must be accessible via keyboard:

- Tab order: Logical left-to-right, top-to-bottom
- Focus visible: Clear 3px outline, 4px offset
- Escape: Close modals, cancel operations
- Enter: Confirm actions, submit forms
- Arrow keys: Navigate menus, sliders, tables

### ARIA Labels

Use ARIA when needed (not always necessary for semantic HTML):

- Buttons: aria-label for icon-only buttons
- Links: aria-label if text is unclear
- Icons: aria-hidden="true" if decorative
- Forms: label associated with input via `for` attribute
- Dynamic content: Use aria-live="polite" for updates

### Reading Order

Ensure content is understandable when read top-to-bottom:

- Headings in proper order (H1 → H2 → H3, not skipping)
- Logical flow without CSS reordering
- Important content before secondary content

### Alternative Text

- Images: Meaningful alt text (not "image1.jpg")
- Icons: aria-label or hidden if decorative
- Charts: Text summary if complex
- Links: Descriptive text, not "click here"

