## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints

Design and test at these viewport widths:

- Mobile: 320px, 375px, 425px
- Tablet: 640px, 768px, 1024px
- Desktop: 1280px, 1440px, 1920px

### Mobile-First Approach

- Start with mobile layout
- Add complexity as screen size increases
- Use min-width media queries (mobile-first)

### Responsive Typography

- Body text: Always 15px on mobile (no smaller)
- Headings: Reduce by 2-4px on mobile, increase on desktop
- Line height: Increase to 1.8 on mobile (readability)
- Container width: 90% with 8px margins on mobile

### Responsive Spacing

- 16px gaps on mobile
- 24px gaps on tablet
- 32px gaps on desktop
- Reduce padding on mobile (12px instead of 24px for cards)

### Responsive Images

- Use `max-width: 100%` with height auto
- Specify aspect ratio to prevent layout shift
- Use srcset for resolution-dependent images
- Compress images before deployment

### Responsive Navigation

See "Navigation & Structure" section above for detailed breakpoint guidelines.

