## Do's and Don'ts

### DO

- ✅ Use the established color palette consistently
- ✅ Follow the typography scale precisely
- ✅ Use 8px multiples for all spacing
- ✅ Maintain visual hierarchy with size and weight
- ✅ Test components across all breakpoints
- ✅ Ensure 4.5:1 color contrast for all text
- ✅ Use semantic HTML for accessibility
- ✅ Provide clear focus states for keyboard users
- ✅ Include loading and error states for all interactions
- ✅ Use consistent button styles and placement
- ✅ Pair colors with text or icons for meaning
- ✅ Use transitions for all interactive changes (0.2s)
- ✅ Test with real content, not lorem ipsum
- ✅ Validate forms inline with clear feedback
- ✅ Use cards to group related content
- ✅ Add generous whitespace around content

### DON'T

- ❌ Don't create custom colors outside the palette
- ❌ Don't use font sizes not in the type scale
- ❌ Don't use weights other than 400, 500, 600, 700
- ❌ Don't use arbitrary spacing (not multiples of 8)
- ❌ Don't rely on color alone to convey information
- ❌ Don't create buttons that look like links (be clear)
- ❌ Don't animate decorative elements
- ❌ Don't use motion faster than 0.3s (feels jerky)
- ❌ Don't create components with contrast below 4.5:1
- ❌ Don't forget about mobile and tablet layouts
- ❌ Don't use more than 2 font families
- ❌ Don't stack modals or create nested modals
- ❌ Don't use placeholder text as labels
- ❌ Don't disable hover states on disabled buttons
- ❌ Don't create layouts that exceed 1440px max width
- ❌ Don't use red for anything except errors or critical actions
- ❌ Don't mix rounded and sharp corners (stay consistent)
- ❌ Don't create text smaller than 12px (readability)
- ❌ Don't forget to test keyboard navigation
- ❌ Don't break the grid system for "special" sections

